TestTool.Model.Resource

Class CourseCollection

  • java.lang.Object
    • TestTool.Model.Resource.CourseCollection

  • public abstract class CourseCollection
extends java.lang.Object
    The collection of Courses available. Currently, this collection is a universal representation of the Courses available for one professors. However, we wish to implement this test tool for multiple professors, and as such, a professor will have ownership over a CourseCollection in a future implementation. This allows our tool to distinguish which professor teaches which courses.

      • changeCourse

        abstract void changeCourse(Course oldC,
                           Course newC)
        Change the given old Course to the given new Course. The old and new records must not be the same. The old record must already be in the CourseCollection. The new Course must meet the same conditions as for the input to the addCourse operation. Typically, the user runs the findCourse operation prior to changeCourse to locate an existing record to be changed.
        Parameters:
        oldC - Course to replace.
        newC - Course to add.

      • deleteCourse

        abstract void deleteCourse(Course course)
        Delete the given Course from the given CourseCollection. The given Course must already be in the CourseCollection. Typically the user runs the findCourse operation prior to deleteCourse to locate an existing record to delete.
        Parameters:
        course - The course to delete.
